zzer Infrastructure + Harnesses

### Strategy
After Phase 1 (proptest) finds the easy/obvious bugs, Phase 2 deploys coverage-guided fuzzing via cargo-fuzz/libFuzzer. This finds DEEP bugs that property-based testing misses because:
1. Coverage guidance: The fuzzer tracks which code paths each input exercises and mutates toward uncovered paths
2. Continuous execution: Fuzz for minutes/hours/days instead of 128-512 fixed cases
3. Corpus evolution: The fuzzer builds a growing corpus of interesting inputs over time
4. Minimization: cargo fuzz tmin automatically shrinks crash inputs to minimal reproducers

### Architecture
```
fuzz/
├── Cargo.toml                    # Separate crate depending on pi_agent_rust with 'fuzzing' feature
├── fuzz_targets/
│   ├── fuzz_smoke.rs             # P2.1: Smoke test
│   ├── fuzz_sse_parser.rs        # P2.2: SSE parser
│   ├── fuzz_sse_stream.rs        # P2.2: SSE stream (UTF-8 layer)
│   ├── fuzz_session_jsonl.rs     # P2.3: Session JSONL file
│   ├── fuzz_session_entry.rs     # P2.3: Session entry JSON
│   ├── fuzz_provider_event.rs    # P2.4: Provider stream events
│   ├── fuzz_message_deser.rs     # P2.5: Message deserialization
│   ├── fuzz_message_roundtrip.rs # P2.5: Message round-trip
│   ├── fuzz_tool_paths.rs        # P2.6: Path traversal
│   ├── fuzz_grep_pattern.rs      # P2.6: Regex DoS
│   ├── fuzz_edit_match.rs        # P2.6: Edit matching
│   ├── fuzz_config.rs            # P2.7: Config parsing
│   ├── fuzz_config_load.rs       # P2.7: Config file loading
│   └── fuzz_extension_payload.rs # P2.8: Extension payloads
└── corpus/                       # P2.9: Seed corpora
    ├── fuzz_sse_parser/
    ├── fuzz_session_jsonl/
    ├── fuzz_provider_event/
    └── ...
```

### Dependency Chain
P2.1 (infrastructure) MUST complete first → then P2.2-P2.8 (harnesses) can proceed in parallel → P2.9 (seed corpus) can proceed once infrastructure is ready but benefits from knowing which harnesses exist.

### Key Technical Decision: fuzzing Feature Flag
The main crate uses #\![forbid(unsafe_code)], but libfuzzer-sys needs unsafe. Solution:
- fuzz/ is a SEPARATE crate (cargo-fuzz's standard layout)
- pi_agent_rust exposes internal APIs under a 'fuzzing' feature flag
- fuzz/Cargo.toml: pi_agent_rust = { path = "..", features = ["fuzzing"] }
- This keeps the main crate safe while allowing fuzzer access to internals

### Run Commands
```bash
cargo fuzz list                                    # List all targets
cargo fuzz run fuzz_sse_parser -- -max_total_time=300  # 5 min run
cargo fuzz run fuzz_sse_parser -- -max_total_time=3600 # 1 hour deep run
cargo fuzz tmin fuzz_sse_parser crash-input.bin     # Minimize crash
cargo fuzz coverage fuzz_sse_parser                # Generate coverage report
```

